text:
<@U0265G76F|iamewald> uploaded a file: <https://uncorked.slack.com/files/iamewald/F1J37G6UX/brandlab-6011.jpg|BrandLab-6011.jpg> and commented: I know we have so many work streams going on with various levels of heads down. In the past month, I also know we’ve had a great deal of excitement and discussion about really LIVING that energy of what a bunch of people blending expertise can mean (aka cross disciplinary work). 

Yes that was very apparent to see in Compass ‘design’ sprints. And I’m excited that if it’s not already happening, we’re shortly going to be remixing the seats. 

But I wanted to share this as an early snapshot of teamwork that happened in Pittsburgh, on behalf of our client Google BrandLab. Jason’s likely on a flight so he can’t get mad that I posted a photo of him (he hates me taking pictures). 

But over this past week, our team — Dennis, Peter, Joel, Emily, Jason, Bryan and me — worked in close collaboration with Google and fabrication partners IonTank. There weren’t roles. There weren’t disciplines so much. There was building, and collaborating, and problem solving, and as the sign says — Making cool shit. 

It was inspiring to see how a project that started as an idea nearly a year ago can translate (with a TON of work) into this bizarre, beautiful thing that is currently being packed up and shipped to San Francisco. It’s nuts, and I can only hope we find a way for everybody to see this thing some day in real life. 

There are two moments that really stick out of a week full of moments/breakthroughs — 

1) 
When our amazing client left, handing the keys to this immense, complex, and very high stakes project to us. He’s always been truthful with us, and walked away saying — “I have complete faith in this team, and feel great about where this is heading.” 

That’s pretty amazing. 

2) 
When two guys from Planar stopped by. They manufacture the square monitors used on this project. They were awestruck and clearly chomping at the bit to do some sort of case study on the BrandLab wall. If I’m being honest, it was funny. They need what we’ve built up over the past year. 

And that was the moment for me. Sometimes I need these as a reminder. Two dudes who are seeing something with fresh eyes, who have both seen a ton of installations with their monitors around the world. 

This one was something that they said — “We’ve never seen anything like this before”

So I wanted to just break through whatever’s happening today to say how wonderful that is. We ARE making stuff that has never been done before, for BrandLab and beyond. I know and feel the weight of all of that, just as everybody does. But it was fun to see it come together naturally in Pittsburgh. 

Thought I’d share. 

Thanks for being here everybody. You’re pretty great.
